The phototoxicity of the porphyrins and conjugates shows an increase with an increase in the irradiation time (Figs. 12
                        , S6). Quaternized complexes are known to strongly interact with polyanionic macromolecules such as DNA [63]. Comparing H2T(3-Py)P and Q-H2T(3-Py)P the quaternized molecule performed better as it was expected. The minimum log reduction value recommended by FDA (Food and Drug Administration) regulations for a potential photosensizers to be applicable for PACT is 3 log CFU [64]. The values for metal free derivatives, Table 4
                        ) are all lower than this value so are not effective for PACT. It has been reported by [65] that the outer membrane of Gram-negative cells contains lipopolysaccharides (LPS) and sialic acid therefore resulting in a surface of more anionic character and consequently results in electrostatic attraction to catanionic porphyrins. Merchat et al. [66] reported that cationic porphyrins meso-tetrakis(N-methylpyridinium-4-yl)porphyrin and meso-tetrakis(N,N,N-trimethylanilinium-4-yl)porphyrin inhibited the growth of Gram-negative bacteria. In our previous study [67] we also reported that In-Cl 5-p-carboxyphenyl-10,15,20-(tris-4-methylpyridyl)-porphyrin triiodide behaved better than unquaternized porphyrin with a log reduction of 9.27.
